.START 

Japan's domestic sales of cars, trucks and buses in September rose 12% from a year earlier to 502,234 units, according to the Japan Automobile Dealers's Association. 

The number of units sold was a record for sales in the month of September, according to the association.
Monthly sales have surpassed previous records in every month this year since March.
Buying has risen 10% for the first nine months of 1989 compared with year-earlier levels. 

Sales of all passenger cars rose 13% from a year earlier to 359,391 units.
Sales of mid-sized cars more than doubled to a record 33,407 units. 

Sales of trucks rose 11% to 140,830 units, also a record.
Bus sales declined by 5.3% to 2,013 units. 

